name: The Cat Cafe
description: The Cat Cafe at The Rail Mall is home to 14 rescue cats with age ranging from 4+ to 6+ years old with great personalities. Experience a relaxing time in a cozy cat cafe or choose the option of a memorable art jamming session with our cats!

name: The Cat Cafe x Art Jamming
description: The Cat Cafe at Bugis is home to 15 rescue cats with age ranging from 8 months to 17 years old+. You will experience a good mix of cats with playful energy to calm and matured personalities in a chill and cozy cafe.

name: Meownistry of Meow
description: We are a cat-friendly co-working space for you to work or play with cats! Feel totally at home with us as you relax whilst a purring kitty lies next to you. Our lounge is made with equal parts open co-working space and foster home. This is a perfect haven for you to catch up with friends after work and pet a kitty while you unwind.

name: Tomoro Coffee (The LINQ)
description: An Indonesian coffee chain known for high-quality and affordable coffee with a variety of modern brews

name: Tomoro Coffee (PLQ 3)
description: An Indonesian coffee chain known for high-quality, affordable coffee and a variety of modern brews

name: The Coach Restaurant
description: A modern new york stakehouse in Singapore

name: Nuldam space
description: a cafe that serves vegan drinks and desserts and lets you write letters to your future self

name: Fortuna terrazza
description: mediterranean seafood, fresh pastas and pizzas, complemented by rich, seasonal ingredients

name: Fernweh
description: work-friendly cafe in chinatown featuring pet-friendly outdoor seating, complimentary wi-fi, and accessible power

name: Styxx
description: newest skewers and grill bar by the founders of leila

name: AM:PM CAFE
description: A cosy dessert spot in Ang Mo Kio known for its soft-serve ice cream served on Hong Kong style egglet waffles. The menu is fully customisable, letting you choose your soft-serve flavour along with toppings and sauces, with popular options like salted caramel, Earl Grey, and blue vanilla. It is open late, until 10:30 pm on most days and midnight on weekends, becoming a popular spot for affordable and Instagram-worthy desserts.

name: Professor Brawn Cafe
description: A warm, meaningful social-enterprise café based in Pathlight School  that offers affordable, comforting meals from steak & eggs to battered fish & chips while employing a largely inclusive workforce of differently-abled adults.

name: Good Bites
description: Good Bites is a halal café serving fusion western dishes that are affordable from burgers, pasta and mains to desserts, all under about $15–$20. The menu also includes healthier options like soups and customisable bowls; for instance, their baked salmon is a highlight. It is open til 5 AM, making it a go-to spot for heartland dining at any hour.

name: The Living Room Cafe
description: The Living Room Café (at Zion Bishan) is a warm, neighbourhood-style café tucked in the Bishan Bible-Presbyterian Church. It has a cozy, laid-back vibe that makes it a great place to chill, work, or catch up with friends. Their menu features comfort food favourites like chicken pot pie, mushroom tom yum pasta, and creamy soups, paired with simple breakfast and brunch options.

name: Filled in the blank
description: Filled in the Blank combines nostalgic Nanyang kopitiam flavours like Mee Siam Nasi Lemak and Curry Chee Cheong Fun with modern creativity. The space is airy and minimalist with unfinished textured walls curved accents and large windows that let in lots of natural light. Their drinks menu includes espresso-based coffees traditional kopi and teh and quirky options like an Iced Kopi Cloud. Open from 7:30 am to 8:30 pm and closed on Mondays it is a perfect spot for a relaxed meal or a quiet coffee break.

name: Cafe Ma Maison (Mandarin Gallery)
description: Café Ma Maison is a cozy Japanese‑Western patisserie café that feels like home. It offers a charming menu of French-inspired tarts classic Japanese cakes like strawberry shortcakes and savoury dishes such as omu‑rice and mentaiko pasta. The décor is nostalgic and warm evoking a relaxed old‑school teahouse vibe designed for lingering chats and sweet treats.

name: SOD Cafe (Hougang)
location: 51 Hougang Ave 9 #01-03 Ci Yuan Community Centre (Singapore 538776)
